        <div class="snippet-answer">
          <p><strong>Bing Webmaster Tools</strong> is Microsoft's free platform for monitoring a website's presence in Bing search results. It surfaces crawl status, index coverage, keyword impressions, backlinks, and site health so owners can diagnose ranking issues and improve visibility across Bing, Yahoo, and Microsoft Copilot. It is the Bing equivalent of <a href="/glossary/google-search-console/">Google Search Console</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="term-meta-strip">
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">US desktop share</div>
            <div class="tms-value">~13% via Bing</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Category</div>
            <div class="tms-value">General Marketing</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Cost</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Free forever</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Difficulty</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Beginner</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="lede-p">Every serious SEO connects Google Search Console. Fewer bother with Bing Webmaster Tools \u2014 which is exactly why it is one of the highest-ROI 20-minute setups in local and organic search. And in 2026, it is your only lever on Microsoft Copilot citations.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is Bing Webmaster Tools?</h2>
        <p>Bing Webmaster Tools (BWT) is Microsoft's free diagnostic and monitoring platform for site owners. Sign in with a Microsoft account, verify your domain, and Bing exposes: how often it crawls your site, which URLs are indexed, which queries drive impressions and clicks, which backlinks point to your domain, and which technical issues are blocking search visibility.</p>
        <p>It is the direct counterpart to <a href="/glossary/google-search-console/">Google Search Console</a>, with a similar UX and a broader feature set in some areas \u2014 including full backlink data (Search Console shows only a sample), a built-in keyword research tool, and site scanning that flags on-page issues automatically.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">One-click Search Console import</div>
          <p>BWT lets you import every verified property from Google Search Console in a single flow. Domain verification, sitemaps, and site settings copy over automatically \u2014 turning a 30-minute manual setup into a 2-minute one.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="why-it-matters">Why Bing Webmaster Tools matters</h2>
        <p>Bing is small compared to Google, but it is not zero \u2014 and its share is where high-intent, high-income searches disproportionately live. Five reasons BWT earns a slot in the stack:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>13%+ of US desktop searches.</strong> Corporate Edge users, government networks, and enterprise workstations default to Bing. B2B pipelines often over-index.</li>
          <li><strong>Microsoft Copilot feed.</strong> Copilot cites from Bing's search index. Fixing crawl and indexing issues in BWT directly improves eligibility for AI-generated citations.</li>
          <li><strong>Free full backlink data.</strong> BWT shows every referring domain \u2014 no sample cap like Search Console \u2014 which makes it a legitimate free backup to Ahrefs / Semrush.</li>
          <li><strong>Built-in <a href="/glossary/keyword-research/">keyword research</a>.</strong> BWT includes a keyword tool with Bing search volumes and related terms \u2014 useful for cross-checking Google-derived data.</li>
          <li><strong>Zero effort, ongoing value.</strong> After the one-time setup, BWT surfaces new indexing and technical issues automatically without further work.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="how-it-works">How Bing Webmaster Tools works</h2>
        <p>The workflow is simple: connect, submit, monitor, act.</p>
        <h3>Step 1 \u2014 Add and verify your site</h3>
        <p>Go to <code>bing.com/webmasters</code>, sign in with a Microsoft account, and add your property. Choose one of three verification methods: DNS TXT record, XML file upload, or a meta tag in the site's <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>. Alternatively, import all Google Search Console properties in one click.</p>
        <h3>Step 2 \u2014 Submit your <a href="/glossary/xml-sitemap/">XML sitemap</a></h3>
        <p>Add your sitemap URL under "Sitemaps". Bing typically discovers and crawls submitted sitemap URLs within 24-72 hours, faster than passive discovery.</p>
        <h3>Step 3 \u2014 Configure IndexNow</h3>
        <p>Bing supports IndexNow \u2014 an open protocol where you notify search engines the moment a URL changes. Enable it in BWT and every content update pings Bing (and Yandex) instantly instead of waiting for the next crawl.</p>
        <h3>Step 4 \u2014 Monitor the six dashboards</h3>
        <p>Search Performance (queries, clicks, impressions), URL Inspection (per-URL crawl status), Sitemaps, Backlinks, Site Explorer (index coverage), and Site Scan (automated on-page audits).</p>
        <h3>Step 5 \u2014 Act on issues</h3>
        <p>BWT surfaces crawl errors, indexation gaps, backlink spikes, and on-page warnings. Fix them the same way you would with Search Console flags: patch, request re-crawl, monitor recovery.</p>

