        <h2 id="examples">Real Bing Webmaster Tools examples</h2>
        <h3>1. Dental practice climbing on Bing local queries</h3>
        <p>A dental practice used BWT to spot that Bing was only crawling 40 of their 120 service pages. They submitted an updated sitemap, enabled IndexNow, and fixed a stray <code>noindex</code> tag flagged by Site Scan. Within eight weeks, 118 pages were indexed and the practice moved from page 3 to top 5 on competitive local Bing queries.</p>
        <h3>2. Ecommerce store fixing crawl budget waste</h3>
        <p>A 10,000-SKU ecommerce store used BWT's URL Inspection and Site Explorer to find Bing wasting crawl budget on filter parameter URLs. They added parameter handling rules in BWT and updated <a href="/glossary/robots-txt/">robots.txt</a>. Bing's average indexing time dropped from weeks to under 72 hours.</p>
        <h3>3. B2B SaaS tracking Copilot citations</h3>
        <p>A B2B SaaS noticed a jump in traffic labeled as "Microsoft Copilot" in analytics. Cross-checking BWT's query data showed Bing surfacing their comparison pages for ChatGPT-vs-competitor queries. They doubled down on comparison content, and Copilot citations grew month over month.</p>

        <h2 id="vs-related">Bing Webmaster Tools vs Bing Places for Business</h2>
        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros-card">
            <h4>Bing Webmaster Tools</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Diagnoses website-wide search visibility</li>
              <li>Crawl, index, and technical SEO data</li>
              <li>Backlinks and keyword performance</li>
              <li>Applies to organic search rankings</li>
              <li>Answer: "Why isn't my site ranking on Bing?"</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons-card">
            <h4><a href="/glossary/bing-places-for-business/">Bing Places for Business</a></h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Manages a single business listing</li>
              <li>NAP, hours, photos, categories</li>
              <li>Local map and business profile visibility</li>
              <li>Applies to Bing Maps and local pack</li>
              <li>Answer: "Is my business found in Bing local?"</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="best-practices">6 Bing Webmaster Tools best practices</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Import from Search Console first.</strong> The one-click import saves 30 minutes of manual setup and copies verified properties instantly.</li>
          <li><strong>Enable IndexNow immediately.</strong> Real-time indexing is Bing's biggest technical edge over Google. Turn it on the day you verify.</li>
          <li><strong>Submit every sitemap variant.</strong> Content sitemap, image sitemap, video sitemap, news sitemap. Bing crawls them independently.</li>
          <li><strong>Run Site Scan monthly.</strong> The automated audit catches indexation errors and on-page issues before they cost rankings.</li>
          <li><strong>Cross-check <a href="/glossary/backlinks/">backlink</a> data.</strong> BWT often shows referring domains Google Search Console does not, filling gaps in your link inventory.</li>
          <li><strong>Monitor Search Performance weekly.</strong> Track the queries driving Bing impressions \u2014 they are often different from Google, revealing intent segments you underserve.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">Common trap \u2014 ignoring Bing indexing gaps</div>
          <p>Sites often assume "if Google indexes it, Bing does too". Bing crawls less aggressively and drops URLs faster than Google. Without BWT surfacing the gap, entire sections of your site can silently disappear from Bing's index while Google shows normal coverage.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="mistakes">Common Bing Webmaster Tools mistakes to avoid</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Verifying and never opening it again.</strong> BWT surfaces new issues weekly. Set a monthly calendar check.</li>
          <li><strong>Skipping IndexNow because "Google doesn't use it".</strong> IndexNow benefits Bing directly, and that flow the Copilot ecosystem.</li>
          <li><strong>Ignoring the keyword tool.</strong> Bing search volumes differ from Google \u2014 often revealing intent gaps.</li>
          <li><strong>Not fixing Site Scan warnings.</strong> Bing weights on-page quality signals like alt text and heading hierarchy more than Google does.</li>
          <li><strong>Assuming zero Bing traffic means zero potential.</strong> Verify first, then measure \u2014 you probably have more Bing impressions than analytics shows.</li>
        </ul>

